main event: Numerous unidentified flying objects were sighted by ground electronic means between 0130 and 0230 on 29 July 1952 in Osceola, Wisconsin.
interesting points: Multiple radar targets, including one large well-defined target moving at 600 knots, were detected,Targets appeared in loose clusters on radar and moved independently with speeds varying from 50 to 600 knots,Some targets were confirmed visually by a pilot who estimated the objects' altitude at 12,500 feet,There was a noted correlation between electronic and visual sightings at the same time,Indicator anomalies prevented definitive analysis of all targets.
sighted object: Unidentified flying objects (UFOs) displayed as radar blips
witness description: Members of the 674th AC&W Squadron, including radar operators and an interceptor pilot.
